<div class="min-h-screen pt-14 pb-10 relative" style="background: transparent;">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 btn btn-secondary group" do %>
        <span class="material-icons transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform">arrow_back</span>
        <span>Back to Home</span>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <article class="glass-thick rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <header class="mb-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Useful Resources</h1>
        <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">Guides, references, and tools worth bookmarking.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Rails Resources</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Rails 8 Documentation",
                    "https://guides.rubyonrails.org/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Still the best place to start when I'm stuck. The guides are actually really well written - I reference the Active Record Query Interface guide at least weekly.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "GoRails",
                    "https://gorails.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Chris Oliver's screencasts have saved me countless hours. When I need to implement something new in Rails, I check here first. His Hotwire content is particularly good.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "The Odin Project - Full Stack Ruby on Rails",
                    "https://www.theodinproject.com/paths/full-stack-ruby-on-rails",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                I recommend this to anyone learning Rails. Even as an experienced dev, I've picked up tricks from their curriculum. Their approach to teaching is spot-on.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Ruby Weekly",
                    "https://rubyweekly.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Every Thursday in my inbox. It's how I keep up with what's happening in Ruby-land without drowning in Twitter/X.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">System Design & Architecture</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-6">
            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "System Design Primer",
                    "https://github.com/donnemartin/system-design-primer",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                This repo is my interview prep bible. But honestly, it's also just great for understanding how real systems work at scale. The diagrams alone are worth bookmarking.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "High Scalability",
                    "http://highscalability.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                Real architecture breakdowns from actual companies. Reading how Discord handles millions of concurrent users or how Uber rebuilt their payment system - that's the good stuff.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
                <%= link_to "Martin Fowler's Blog",
                    "https://martinfowler.com/",
                    target: "_blank",
                    rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                    class: "hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors",
                    style: "color: var(--text-primary);" %>
              </h3>
              <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                When Fowler writes, I read. His posts on microservices and event sourcing shaped how I think about service boundaries. Plus, he explains complex patterns in a way that actually makes sense.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Development Environment & Tools</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">My Current Setup (2025)</h3>
            
            <div class="mb-6">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-3" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Hardware:</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 ml-6" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                <li>MacBook Pro 14" M3 Pro - The battery life is insane, I can code all day at a coffee shop</li>
                <li>LG 34" Ultrawide (34WN80C-B) - Game changer for having multiple files open side-by-side</li>
                <li>Keychron K2 - Brown switches, not too clicky but satisfying</li>
                <li>Logitech MX Master 3S - The horizontal scroll wheel is perfect for long code files</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-medium mb-3" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Essential Dev Tools:</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 ml-6" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
                <li>VS Code with vim bindings - Best of both worlds</li>
                <li>iTerm2 + Oh My Zsh - Can't live without my git branch in the prompt</li>
                <li>TablePlus - So much better than pgAdmin for database work</li>
                <li>Insomnia - Cleaner than Postman for API testing</li>
                <li>Fork - Sometimes you just need a GUI for complex rebases</li>
                <li>OrbStack - Way faster than Docker Desktop on Mac</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="glass-thin rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">About This Site</h2>
          <p class="mb-4" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
            These are the resources I actually use and reference regularly. As a backend engineer focused on Rails, I'm always looking for ways to level up - whether that's diving deeper into distributed systems, keeping up with Rails 8 features, or just finding fun ways to keep programming interesting outside of work.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
            If you've got recommendations for resources I should check out, I'd love to hear them. Always looking to expand this list with genuinely useful stuff.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

